The paper discusses load balancing in Fog networks, which is a subfield of computer networking. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a reinforcement learning-based decision-making process, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Software-Defined Network (SDN) in Fog computing, which is a subfield of distributed computing (cs.DC). The proposed algorithm involves decision-making and optimization, which falls under the subfield of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithmic framework, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well.
